Package com.mycompany.a3

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ICollection
    This interface is used by the GameCollection class to make sure it has the ability to add a game object to the collection and return an iterator.
    ICollider
    ICollider interface to handle collisions.
    IDrawable
    IDrawable interface to handle drawing of objects.
    IIterator
    This interface is used by the GameIterator class in GameCOllection to make sure it has the ability to loop through the indexes of a game collection.
    ISelectable
    ISelectable interface to handle selection of objects.
    ISteerable
    This interface is used by the Ant class to control its steering left and right.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AboutCommand
    This class holds the logic when the About command is invoked.
    AccelerateCommand
    This class holds the logic when the Accelerate command is invoked.
    Ant
    This class contains the Ant Object.
    BGSound
    Class that handles looping sound
    BrakeCommand
    This class holds the logic when the Brake command is invoked.
    ClockTickCommand
    This class holds the logic when the Tick command is invoked.
    ExitCommand
    This class holds the logic when the Exit command is invoked.
    Fixed
    This abstract class contains Fixed objects that are unable to move and extends GameObject.
    Flag
    This class contains the Flag object that extends the fixed objects since it is motionless.
    FoodStation
    This class contains the FoodStation object that extends the fixed objects since it is motionless.
    Game
    This Class creates the game world and plays the game.
    GameCollection
    This is the game collection class which implements Icollection.
    GameObject
    This is the abstract parent class that contains the Game Objects.
    GameWorld
    This class initializes the objects in the game world and handles the logic of the game.
    HelpCommand
    This class holds the logic when the Help command is invoked.
    LeftTurnCommand
    This class holds the logic when the Left Turn command is invoked.
    MapView
    This class includes the display of the map and styles the center container.
    Movable
    This class contains the movable objects and extends Game Object.
    PauseCommand
    Pause Command to handle when the user pauses.
    PositionCommand
    Position command to handle when the user clicks an object.
    RightTurnCommand
    This class holds the logic when the Right command is invoked.
    ScoreView
    This class includes the display of the scoreview and styles the top scoreview UI.
    Sound
    Sound class to play the game sounds.
    SoundCommand
    This class holds the logic when the Sound command is invoked.
    Spider
    This class contains the Spider Object.
    Starter
    Codename One Generated starter class.
